
[1]wholesome

   WHOLESOME, a. [G.]

   1. Tending to promote health; favoring health; salubrious; as wholesome
   air or diet; a wholesome climate.

   2. Sound; contributing to the health of the mind; favorable to morals,
   religion or prosperity; as wholesome advice; wholesome doctrines;
   wholesome truths.
